This document contains the step used to create this project.

1. Template web app created to run on port 8080
2. Docker file added to run the app in container
3. Requirements.txt added to the repo containing app dependencies
4. To make the image run the command docker build -t myproject .
5. To check the created container run command docker images
6. To run the image into a container, run the command docker run -d -p 8080:8080 myproject
7. Now check the app by going to http://127.0.0.1:8080 in browser.
8. Convert the json to csv.


9. Now we have to prepare our Cassandra image
  docker pull cassandra:latest
  docker run --name cassandra-db -d cassandra:latest
  docker cp facts.csv cassandra-db:/home/facts.csv
  docker exec -it cassandra-db cqlsh
  CREATE KEYSPACE facts WITH REPLICATION = {'class' : 'SimpleStrategy', 'replication_factor' : 1};
  CREATE TABLE facts.data (id text PRIMARY KEY, fact text, , type text, first_name text, last_name text, upvotes int);
  COPY facts.data (id, fact, type, first_name, last_name, upvotes) FROM '/home/facts.csv' WITH DELIMITER=',' AND HEADER=TRUE;
  Select * From facts.data
  docker stop `docker ps -l -q`
  docker commit -m "Cassendra with data" `docker ps -l -q` cassandra/facts:v1


10.
